      "raw_text": "The law firm of Robertson, Miller g.\nRosenhaupt have taken up another\ncause against the Northern Pacific and\nask the court for $4,000 The plaintiff\nis John j. Peters. Peters was a brake\nmen in the employ of the Northern Pa\ncifc in December, 1901, and was Sc\nyerely injured in a wreck north Of\nNorth Yakima, losing an arm and suf-\nfering other injuries as a result of\nwhich he is unable TO earn a living."
